                        Preface

        1. If you use TR to trace a program having Turbo Debug infor-

mation, you can use 'g _main' to begin.

        2. TR supports 32bit registers. Refer to the R32 command.

        3. After TR terminates, all int vectors hooked by user program

will be restored and all memory freed.

        4. TR can auto use XMS to free more conventional memory.

        5. All numeric input is hexadecimal.



TR needs 80386 CPU or above to run. TR can run under simple DOS,

Windows or Windows 95/98 dos box ( will be a little slower ), with

himem.sys or emm386.exe or any other XMS/EMS memory manager programs.

TR can work with Soft-ICE active. TR can only trace DOS programs running

in real mode. TR knows nothing about Protected Mode or Windows programs.

If you want to trace Dos Protected Mode program(DPMI),16bit NE,32bit PE

Windows programs, try TR for Win95 at

        http://trw.yeah.net            



